## 5) IMPLEMENTED CHANGES (actual code edits)
These are the real edits done for auth readiness.

## 5.1 `utils/session.ts`
What changed:
- Added centralized session keys list:
  - `token`
  - `user_data`
  - `wallet_secret`
  - `wallet_pubkey`
  - `wallet_pin_hash`
  - `cached_pin`
  - `cached_pin_expiry`
- Added helper:
  - `persistAuthSession(token, user)` to store token + user payload consistently.
- Updated `clearSession()`:
  - now clears all listed keys via `Promise.allSettled`.
  - avoids failing whole logout/session-clear on one storage delete error.

Why:
- Consistent auth state handling.
- Less duplication.
- Better crash safety during session cleanup.

---

## 5.2 `contexts/AuthContext.tsx`
What changed:
- `logout()` switched from manual multi-key deletes to `clearSession()` helper.
- Wrapped with `try/finally` so in-memory token/state still reset even if storage operations have issues.

Why:
- Single source of truth for session clearing.
- Idempotent and safer logout behavior.

---

## 5.3 `services/api.ts`
What changed:
- Introduced `ApiError` type with optional `status`.
- Added `getErrorMessage(response)`:
  - safely handles JSON and non-JSON error bodies.
- Added `parseSuccessResponse(response)`:
  - handles `204` and empty responses gracefully.
- Reworked request header handling:
  - uses `Headers` object
  - always sets `Content-Type`
  - sets `Authorization` only when token exists
- Fixed 401 flow:
  - call `clearSession()`
  - call registered `authLogout()` if available (error-tolerant)
  - redirect to `/(auth)/login`
- Updated `post()` / `put()`:
  - avoid passing `body: undefined` under strict TS option behavior.

Why:
- Eliminates auth-flow fragility.
- Prevents parsing-related crashes on unexpected responses.
- Ensures deterministic unauthorized-session cleanup.

---

## 5.4 `app/(auth)/login.tsx`
What changed:
- Removed direct SecureStore writes; now uses `persistAuthSession`.
- Added `getLoginErrorMessage()` for better user-facing error mapping.
- Added duplicate-submit guard:
  - early return if `isLoading` is true.
- Normalized login identifier once:
  - `emailOrUsername = email.trim()`.
- Changed username/email input keyboard type:
  - `email-address` -> `default` (better for mixed username/email input).
- Removed login-time Terms checkbox + gating.
- Login button now disabled only while loading (`disabled={isLoading}`).
- Kept lightweight haptics and existing UI structure.

Why:
- Faster login UX (less friction).
- Better reliability against double taps.
- Cleaner auth persistence flow.

---

## 5.5 `app/(auth)/signup.tsx`
What changed:
- Removed direct SecureStore writes; now uses `persistAuthSession`.
- Added helper constants:
  - `USERNAME_REGEX = /^[a-zA-Z0-9_]+$/`
  - `EMAIL_REGEX = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/`
- Added `getSignupErrorMessage()`.
- Added duplicate-submit guard (`isLoading` check).
- Normalized signup values:
  - username trimmed
  - email trimmed + lowercased
- Added frontend validation aligned with backend:
  - username required, 3–30 chars, allowed chars regex
  - email required and format check
  - password min length 6
  - confirm password match
  - Terms acceptance required
- Updated signup request payload to normalized values.
- Password hint changed from strict/complex wording to:
  - `Minimum 6 characters` (matches backend reality).
- Signup button disabled when either:
  - terms not accepted
  - loading in progress

Why:
- Reduces unnecessary server round trips.
- Keeps frontend behavior consistent with backend policy.
- Improves stability and clarity for users.

---

## 5.6 `soulwallet-backend/src/server.ts`
What changed (auth-readiness related):
- Added:
  - `app.set('trust proxy', 1)`
- Updated JSON parser:
  - `express.json({ limit: '1mb' })`
- Split auth rate limiting:
  - `registerLimiter` (stricter, max 8 / 15 min)
  - `loginLimiter` (max 20 / 15 min, `skipSuccessfulRequests: true`)
- Applied:
  - `/register` -> `registerLimiter`
  - `/login` -> `loginLimiter`

Why:
- Practical production-ish readiness under proxy.
- Better anti-abuse behavior without penalizing valid repeated login use.
- Keeps beta scope reasonable (not enterprise-complex).

